title: Summary of problem with the LI21 BL01 IOC
text: Shantha and Allan tried to swap the acromag card first, but this did not fix the problem. Communication to TD-11 still was not working. After discussion with Mike Harms it was decided to take two actions: 1.) Swap the 8-slot crate with an older 2-slot crate and try to see if the new acromag card would connect 2.) Swap the CPU They tried step 1., but this did not fix the problem. After this, they put the original acromag card back and tried step 2, but realized that the CPU spare they brought did not fit into the older 2-slot crate, so they put the CPU into the original 8-slot crate. This configuration worked! After tightening down the cables and seating the modules well, they turned on the crate and connection was restored to TD-11.
